<p>face to the enemy.<br/>We have just received three bags of mail &amp; I am waiting patiently for them to be sorted to see if I have any luck</p>
<p>I see by your letter that Kit has started he[r] nasty tricks again I'm sure that one of these fine days she will wake up to the fact that her ruses are not sportmanlike &amp; will drop them alltogether.</p>
<p>Say Mother give my best love to Maidie &amp; tell her I am still keeping in good health &amp; I wish her &amp; all the rest of their family the best of health &amp; happiness. I sent a couple of postcard Photos to Maid one of which is for you.</p>
<p>Well Mother Dear I must now say Good bye for it may be some time before I will be able to write you again also keep up a strong heart &amp; don't worry every opportunity I get I will drop a line &amp; let you know how things are in general. Say Mother thank Mr Lloyd on my behalf for his kindness to you.</p>
<p>Good bye Mother Dear &amp; may God Bless &amp; keep you in good health &amp; happiness in your old age.</p>
<p>Your Ever Loving Son<br/>xxxxxxx Will xxxxxx<br/>xxxxxxxxxx</p>
<p>[Note in red at the bottom of the page:]<br/>Sgt. Major Schaeffer killed in trenches at Anzac 20th May, 1915.</p>
